{
  "text": "The presentation of wide complex tachycardia can pose a diagnostic dilemma for the clinician, with significant differences in choice of treatment depending on the etiology of the arrhythmia. Most wide complex tachycardias are the result of ischemic heart disease and should be identified and treated according to current guidelines on pharmacologic and therapeutic interventions. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] The differential diagnosis for these arrhythmias also may include supraventricular tachycardia with aberrancy and idiopathic ventricular tachycardia.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "32096189",
    "[CITATION_2]": "38193214"
  },
